  "body": "Geth version: `Geth/v1.5.0-unstable-6952fe3a/linux/go1.7`\nOS & Version: Linux Debian Jessie\n\nI'm synced with the `Morden` network, but the geth do not exists from the syncing status. I have tried resync and few times restarting the client but i have every time the same result. The client thinks that we have much more blocks than reality.\n\nI have tried parity 1.4.0 unstable, but has the completely same issue.\n\n```\n> eth.syncing\n{\n  currentBlock: 1787866,\n  highestBlock: 1789152,\n  knownStates: 0,\n  pulledStates: 0,\n  startingBlock: 1782999\n}\n```\n\n```\n> admin.peers.forEach(function(a){console.log('client:'+a.name);})\nclient:Ethereum(J)/v1.3.6/Linux/Release/Java/Dev\nclient:Geth/v1.5.0-unstable-6952fe3a/linux/go1.5.1\nclient:Geth/v1.4.17-stable-5a6008e0/linux/go1.7.1\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable/linux/go1.5.1\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable/linux/go1.5.1\nclient:Geth/v1.5.0-unstable-084a8ece/linux/go1.6.2\nclient:Geth/v1.5.0-unstable/linux/go1.5.1\nclient:Parity/v1.3.8-beta-e0778fc-20161015/x86_64-linux-gnu/rustc1.12.0\nclient:Geth/v1.4.10-stable/windows/go1.6.2\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable-c72f5459/linux/go1.6\nclient:Geth/v1.4.12-stable-421df866/darwin/go1.7.1\nclient:Parity/v1.4.0-unstable-cceca91-20161015/x86_64-linux-gnu/rustc1.12.0\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable-c72f5459/windows/go1.7\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable/linux/go1.5.1\nclient:Geth/v1.5.0-unstable-b19b7c39/linux/go1.5.3\nclient:Parity/v1.3.8-beta-e0778fc-20161015/x86_64-linux-gnu/rustc1.12.0\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable-c72f5459/windows/go1.7\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable-c72f5459/linux/go1.7\nclient:Parity/v1.3.8-beta/x86_64-linux-gnu/rustc1.12.0\nclient:Parity/v1.3.8-beta/x86_64-linux-gnu/rustc1.12.0\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable/linux/go1.5.1/EtherMiner_#K160320\nclient:Geth/v1.4.16-stable-68815256/linux/go1.7\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable-c72f5459/darwin/go1.7\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable/linux/go1.5.1\nclient:Geth/v1.4.18-stable/linux/go1.6.2\n```\n\nMore logs:\nhttps://gist.github.com/i