    "body": "I have a geth client on my desktop PC (windows 10)with full synced morden chain, and i have a VPS(debian jessie) with Geth/v1.5.0-unstable-6952fe3a/linux/go1.7 client. When on the desktop PC have (example) 1790369 block number and the eth.syncing returns false then on my VPS have the same block number but eth.syncing returns that i'm need to be synced with ~1000 blocks more.\nI think this happens because with the Hard Fork has the morden network divided to 2 chain. One with the old `HF not supported` clients and one with the `HF` clients on the same chain.\n",
