    "body": "Yeah, so I kind of figured it out. The reason geth things we have much more blocks, is because someone actually mined a ton of blocks (3000+) on the non forked testnet. This causes fast sync to always try to sync to that chain, fail, drop the offending peer, try again. But since there are a ton of peers still persisting the old non forked testnet, there's always someone feeding junk.\n\nThis could have been avoided with a similar protective measure that we did for the dao fork, but I haven't considered it since it was obvious the main network would move forward to the fork. I didn't think the testnet would have issues with old miners.\n",
